<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="bright-adj">bright <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /braɪt/    美 /braɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>明亮的；阳光明媚的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a large bright room
明亮的大房间</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The weather is bright and sunny. 
天气晴朗，阳光明媚。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(颜色) 鲜艳的；鲜亮的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I never wear bright colours. 
我从来不穿鲜艳的衣服。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>欢快的；生气勃勃的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her face was <strong>bright with</strong> happiness. 
她的脸上洋溢着幸福的笑容。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>聪明的；伶俐的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He was bright and curious about the world outside his hometown. 
他天资聪颖，对家乡以外的世界很好奇。</p><footer>译林② – 3</footer></div>

<h4 id="5-promising">5.<strong>(前途) 光明的 (promising)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You <strong>have a bright future</strong>. 
你前途光明。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>brighten /'braɪtn/ v <br />
brightly /brightly/ adv   </p></div>